Unsourced material may be challenged and removed. *Find sources:* "Lim Chu Kang Camp II" – news **·** newspapers **·** books **·** scholar **·** JSTOR *(December 2019)* *(Learn how and when to remove this message)* **Lim Chu Kang Camp II** is located at [Lim Chu Kang](/wiki/Lim_Chu_Kang) in the northwest part of [North Region, Singapore](/wiki/North_Region,_Singapore). The camp is operated by the [Republic of Singapore Air Force](/wiki/Republic_of_Singapore_Air_Force) and located on Lim Chu Kang Road opposite [Choa Chu Kang Cemetery](/wiki/Choa_Chu_Kang_Cemetery). The camp houses elements from Singapore Air Defense Artillery 163 Squadron (Medium altitude air defence) and 160 Squadron. This article about a Singapore building or structure is a stub.
